{
  "version": 2,
  "builds": [
    {
      "src": "server.js",
      "use": "@vercel/node",
      "config": {
        "includeFiles": [
          "db/**",
          "routes/**",
          ".env",
          "server.js"
        ],
        "maxDuration": 10 // Max duration badha di hai, taaki DB connection timeout na ho
      }
    }
  ],
  "routes": [
    {
      "src": "/api/(.*)",
      "dest": "/server.js"
    },
    {
      "src": "/(.*)",
      "dest": "/server.js"
    }
  ]
}
```
* **Kyunki:** Serverless environment mein, Express ko `db/db.js` aur `routes/orderRoutes.js` jaisi files ko load karne ki zarurat hoti hai. **`"includeFiles"`** Vercel ko batata hai ki deploy karte samay in files ko bhi package mein shamil karein.

